inn1.comm: short outside off, Strauss chases it straight away but doesn't make contact
down the leg side this time and that's the first run of the day, poor start from Powell
better line on off stump, pushed at the ball and gets a thick inside down into his boot and it rolls into the leg side
back of a length on off stump, opens the face and runs it away to backward point
oh my goodness, that's awful, a huge wide outside off, it barely hit the cut strip and would have been a wide in Test cricket
straighter this time, worked nicely off middle stump through midwicket and well timed...the outfield doesn't look too quick and Strauss has to test that hamstring has he runs three
adjusts to the right hander, on off stump and Bopara turns his first ball to midwicket
fuller on off stump, well played by Bopara as he leans forward and opens the face to find the gap at square cover to launch his account
good start, on off stump and Strauss opens the face and runs it to backward point
down the leg side and another extra to the total
that one stops a little on Strauss as he turns it to the leg side and nearly gets a leading edge...signs of things to come?
width outside off, slashed over the slips and down to third man
that's a good one, testing line outside off draws Bopara forward who plays a lazy push and almost gets an edge
he's behind the line of this one, defending down towards mid-off
another wide, dragged outside off and an easy decision for Aleem Dar
pushed into the off side, but another long over
pushed across the left hander, Strauss lets this one go through
pushed into the off side without much timing
more width on this one, cut away hard down to third man
well, well, this one keeps low and scoots through past Bopara's off stump...interesting sign so early in the game
another wide, banging in short but goes down the leg side, Powell's problems from the Test series continue but of course become even more apparent in one-day cricket
full on off stump, driven sweetly and very straight but goes straight into the stumps and the non-striker's end so is denied at least a run
oh dear, poor stuff, another big wide down the leg side
better line, Bopara comes forward and gets an inside edge into his body which bobbles into the off side
pushed down to mid on
comes into the front foot, defended square onto the off side
plays this on the move as he takes a stride down the pitch, loses a bit of control of his bat and gets a thick outside edge down to third man
I've lost count of the wides already, this one is a tighter call but is well outside off stump

oh boy, chaos as Bopara gets an inside edge into his pads which rolls towards backward point. He wants the single, then he doesn't, and would have been miles out if Darren Sammy's throw had hit the non-striker's stumps
worked off his hip down to fine leg
full on off stump, driven firmly back to Edwards to they hurls it back past the stumps and almost beats Denesh Ramdin who has to dive to save four overthrows
driven into the covers but without much timing, but he has the chance to scamper a single
worked off the stumps to midwicket
banged in shorter, gets Bopara in a bit of a tangle with bat and gloves and fends it ungainly into the leg side
nice use of the wrists, turned past square leg and initially Bopara wanted two but some swift work from Bravo keeps them to a single...he's a brilliant fielder
nicely bowled, that's the area to Strauss, full outside off and he doesn't get a great stride into the shot and gets beaten
short and wide, Strauss hammers a cut shot square but Bravo is again in the action with a brilliant full-length dive that cuts two off the run count
dropped into the leg side, a sharp single which is all very pretty but there hasn't been an attempt at anything aggressive so far
driven out to extra cover
another thick outside edge down to third man, timing already looks hard work
defended square on the off side
slower ball full on off stump, Bopara comes forward and plays it gently into the leg side where Edwards fields in his follow through
a much better over this time, finishes with a tight ball on off stump which is defended to mid-off
dragged down outside off and Powell concedes another wide...how much longer can Gayle let this carry on?
nicely whipped off middle stump but he picks out the man at square leg
tries to chop this through the off side but gets a bottom edge back past his stumps and Ramdin collects
there's the first boundary of the day, a lovely off drive by Strauss as he leans into the shot and finds the gap between cover and mid-off

he's gone this time, and it's a bit of a shocker, as he gets a toe end on a horribly short and wide ball that he could barely reach...the ball looped to Bravo at backward point who took a simple catch, but that was woeful cricket from bowler and batsman
outside off and left alone
oh dear, on dear...this is an awful ball, fired way down the leg side and Ramdin can't even reach it. Some nifty footwork at fine leg prevents a boundary
defended down to mid-on to end an fairly ordinary over which somehow earned a wicket
outside off and Pietersen watches his first ball go through
nicely whipped from outside off, sweetly timed but picks out mid-on
back of a length, defended to the bowler who collects in his follow through
and he's away with a neat turn off his body through square leg, rolled his wrists nicely to keep it down
the ball is coming so slowly off the surface, Bopara pushes this one square past backward point and collects two down to third man
poor delivery and well played, loses his line on leg stump and Bopara flicks it past fine leg who is inside the circle...very neat stroke from Bopara for his first boundary
driven without much timing and it rolls into the non-striker's stumps
misses a flick to leg and the ball takes the pad into the leg side
better line, Pietersen comes across his crease and defends back to Powell
nice shot, flicked from outside off into the leg side but he can't beat an athletic dive and collects just a single
short...wide...hammered, that's more like it as Bopara latches onto a hint of width and thumps it through the off side with real power
tries to work this leg side but gets an inside edge...just a strangled shout from Powell
turned through the leg side, placed in front of square so there is time to come back for a second
lovely timing on this one, too straight and Pietersen flicks it through midwicket and Pollard at deep square leg can't get around
driven on the up, but that's difficult on this surface and it rolls to mid-on
turned into the leg side
he feels he missed out on this one as he drives powerfully down the ground but can't find the gap
worked from straight and picks out the man at deep square, brings up England's fifty at the end of the first Powerplay
driven firmly down to mid-off
innovation from Pietersen as he walks at Bravo outside off then flicks this through midwicket...a lot of effort for one run
cut into the off side but he can't get any timing
whipped from off stump and Bopara nearly takes out his team-mate as Pietersen is hit on the wrist at the non-striker's end
guided away down to third man
full ball and Pietersen thumps a straight drive but can't get it further than mid-on
starts with a slower ball on off stump, defended into the off side
played square on the off side, an appeal from Sammy who thinks it might be pad first but no one else is interested
opens the face and runs it to third man, there will be a lot of that today
outside off, worked back to the bowler
whipped sweetly from off stump down to long on who is protecting the boundary
this time Bopara works down the ground, steady start from Sammy
outside off, Bopara has a slash without much footwork
defended into the off side as Bravo mixes up his variety of slower balls
oops, that comes out wrong and is well wide of the stumps
and another wide, poor stuff this time from Bravo as England are gifted another run
that's the line, on off stump, driven straight at mid-off and he gets off for a single straight away. It was a good call and he was always safe
and Pietersen unleashes the shot of the day, drives straight down the ground from a full delivery and sends this all the way for the first six
but he goes next ball, done by the lack of pace as the ball stops on the surface, he goes to turn it to the leg side and gets a leading edge that loops to mid-on
outside off, left alone, stays low through to Ramdin
turned into the leg side for a comfortable single
outside off, defended to backward point
wristily worked down to third man to get off the mark
turned down the on side, Sammy dives across in his follow through and fields
worked off the stumps into the square leg area to rotate the strike
well bowled, comes back into Shah quite late and he defends to the off side
on off stump, defended straight down the pitch
worked towards midwicket, Bopara seems keen for one but is sent back...these two will make for interesting running!
he goes ariel, drives high over mid-on with a straight bat...not quite timed but has enough on it to clear the fielder and run over the rope
slower ball outside off, driven out to point
short on leg stump, flicked off his hip to short fine leg and he has overstepped as well
flicked over the leg side and he picks out deep square leg, some people think it's out but instead it's just a single...so much action
another slower ball, driven down to third man
angling into the right-hander who pushes it back to the bowler
punched with no timing or power to cover
a good slower ball which forces him to mistime his little flicky shot to leg
fuller delivery which he works to mid-on
back-cut late down to third man
nudged to leg for a single
dropped down to the off side for a zero

caught in two minds here, and possibly three. He thought about pulling, and realised it was a slower ball. He then thought about defending, but was still itching to pull it - so it was in between the two and earned him nothing
shorter ball which he rides and works to leg
flicked to leg
an elegant and free-flowing cover drive
shorter and paddled to fine leg
flicked to leg
paddly flick to leg
pushed back past to the bowler
this holds up on the batsman who drives, the ball falling short of mid-off
too straight, worked around the corner
ooh beaten! Quicker ball from the man they call Nikita, you wouldn't want to meet her, and it passes by his outside edge
cut to point
actual runs for Shah here - a superb shot, creaming this on the front foot past a diving mid-off
Shah goes on the pull but he's going home alone as it drifts down the leg side
chopped to third man
tries to whip this around the corner
slower ball whipped to leg
flighted outside off, he tries to chop it out to third man but somehow can't
fuller delivery and very well bowled. A touch fuller. Chippily driven to mid-on
gives himself room, punching it out to cover
steps to leg and milks another single to cover
nicely played - onto the front foot, nurdling it to leg
driven to long-on this time
tries to work it through midwicket but can't time it
fuller ball and expertly chopped to third man. Great skills there from Shah
nicely bowled, Sammy. Very full and spearing into his middle stump, all he can do is dig it out
beautifully back-cut but third man retrieves
nudged to leg
and it's driven to long-on for another jogged single
flatter ball on leg stump and turned to leg
tossed up on middle-and-leg, he drives to long-on once more
turn and bounce! Beautifully bowled - beat him in the flight and it turned, bounced and squared Shah up. That would've been comfortably taken at first slip
flighted on middle, he's forward and defending
pushed back to the bowler
nicely squeezed past cover
pushed out to the off side
tries to sweep but can't time it
short, wide and cut to point
goes for a powerful slap but he can't break the covers
wristily flicked to leg
Bopara waits for it before turning it to leg

got him! Nikita has a wicket. Spearing into him, it straightened on middle-and-leg while Bopara was trying to flick it to fine-leg and he was beaten by a touch of turn ... and it slid onto him quite a bit quicker than he was expecting, too
angling into Collingwood's legs who bunts it to long-on for a single
flicked out to the off side
goes on the drive and opens the face at the very last moment. Neatly played. Amazingly flexible wrists
chopped out to cover
outside off, Shah tries to do a Pietersen and whip it through midwicket but gets an outside edge. Give over
defensively driven to long-on
defended on the front foot
Collingwood stands tall to this good-length delivery, punching it out to the off side
worked to leg
outside off, he angles it past point
worked out to the off side
Shah steps outside the off stump and flicks it to leg
tossed up outside the off stump, Collingwood's forward and defending out to point
defended out to the off side
Collingwood's paddling and gets a single to fine leg. Woops! He's gone down like a sack of spuds, but he's up again quickly and manages to get two
pushed out to the off side
worked back to the bowler
worked to leg
excellent line outside off, worked to the off side
down the leg side and flicked around the corner
driven out to long-off
fuller length and worked to leg
down the leg side but Shah can't get a run here, the ball stroking to mid-on
tosses it up and he comes forward to defend
ooh, bit lucky there. Goes for a paddle and top-edges it ... only just evading the running slip
tossed up and driven to mid-off
smacked to cover
tossed up on middle-and-leg
nudged to leg
pushed back to the bowler
excellent length. He really is remarkably disciplined this guy
flicked to mid-on
good line just outside off, and again Shah can't get a run
again blocked to leg
flicked through midwicket
tossed up on middle and flicked to mid-on. Sorry, long-on
over the top for four! Classy shot. Down the pitch and he opened the face, flicking and driving over cover - really difficult shot to play
poor line and he steals a single down the leg side
too straight again and he works it to leg
tossed up on middle, he's forward defending
down the leg side and worked through midwicket
hammered through the off side out to the man at deep cover
defended from the crease into the off side, tight line from Sammy
worked off the stumps out to deep square-leg
driven through the off side, ticking over with singles at the moment
full on the stumps, worked out to midwicket
loses his line on leg stump, flicked neatly past short fine leg and it races away...poor delivery from Sammy with the field he has
turned out to midwicket
bunted down to long on, another jogged single
tries to reverse sweep, not very elegant and gets into a tangle, an appeal from Miller but it might just have been outside off stump
tucked into the leg side
worked out through deep square-leg
defended back to the bowler, decent over from Miller
pushed into the off side, Chanderpaul is quick but Collingwood had plenty of time as the throw came in
opens the face into the covers, Shah shakes his hand again...remember he cramps up quite easily
nice straight bat, driven down to long off
picks out Chanderpaul at cover this time
goes on side, midwicket comes around and keeps them to a single
popped into the leg side, in the air but nowhere near a fielder and it's a single to long on
lovely shot from Collingwood, a chip over midwicket, one of his strengths, and it beats the man in the deep
comes forward and defends
pushed back to the bowler who collides with with Shah and takes him down with a fine rugby tackle
superbly played by Collingwood, comes down and chips over midwicket again with enough timing to beat the boundary rider
pushed down to long on
way down the leg side, a big wide...West Indies have been poor in that department today
turned into the leg side to end an expensive over
gentle medium pace, tucked off the stumps backward of square on the leg side
tucked into the gap at midwicket
guided down to third man
driven nicely into the off side, picks out the sweeper and that brings up his half century. A good innings from Shah, off 67 balls
defended into the leg side
slower ball, full outside off, driven down to long off
tucked into the leg side
can't beat the field
very full, dug out back to Gayle
tickled down to short fine-leg
pushed down to long on
big appeal from Gayle as Shah gets taken on the pad but umpire Dar isn't interested...tidy start from Gayle
angled down to third man
drives and gets a thick inside edge to the leg side, fumble from Miller means the single is comfortable
poor ball, way down the leg side, Ramdin can't stop it and that's five to the total...bonus runs for England
short and wide outside off, Collingwood rocks back and cracks it through point for four more
better line, pushed back to the bowler
pushed down to long on
dropped into the off side, good sharp single, 13 off the over to boost England
fires it on the leg stump
a wasteful leg-side wide
nicely turned through midwicket
down the leg side again and Collingwood nudges it through midwicket. But only for a single. Shah's not the quickest...
a punchy drive out to the off side
on middle-and-leg, easily nurdled for another jogged single
walks into this extravagant flick to mid-on but a good stop prevents a single
the wrong line again, down leg
full, straight and defended. Much better delivery
takes this from outside off and works it for a single through midwicket
huge shout but it's turned down! Wow that's close. It cut back a touch on Collingwood and beat his flick to leg. That did look absolutely dead...
defended solidly
nicely nudged around leg for a single
Collingwood drives this, with immense bottom hand, wide of mid-off to long-off
tossed up and bashed to cover
brilliant shot. A horrid bumper from Gayle, wanging it in the pitch outside off, but Shah drove this on the up by opening the face and guided it beautifully behind square for four
again he opens the face for a single
a wide down the leg side
wide and he cuts, but can't get a single
pushed to mid-on
on middle he works it to leg
very good length, pushed out just for a single
down the pitch and bunts this for a single out to the off side
down the leg side
flicked to short fine leg and Shah, a compulsive runner, sets off for a single but is roared back in his crease by Collingwood
pushes this back to the bowler
bashed back to the bowler
fullish and Collingwood digs it out to long-on
Collingwood goes down on one knee and attempts an ugly, cross-batted swipe which yields just a single
very well bowled - a quicker one at nearly 79mph which swings back late into the right-hander who can only smudge it to leg
another full toss which Collingwood can't capitalise on
down the leg side, he tries to get bat on it but he can't! West Indies must be loving this
got him! A bit too full to pull, but that's what Shah tried to do and could only top-edge to the wicketkeeper - and that's Bravo's 100th ODI wicket
down the leg side
nervously jabbed to the leg side, and a little uppishly too, but it's short of the short midiwkcet
that is so out. Utterly out. Emphatically dead in front of middle-and-off. It cut back a bit, and Mascarenhas didn't even bother to look back at the umpire
nudged to leg
turned to the on side
cuts this straight to point
squared up a touch and it takes a thick outside edge
worked to leg
excellent ball swinging in on the off stump, driven to long-on
really good slower ball on middle-and-leg
ooh that's a good'un, cutting back sharply on him and coming off his pads
squeezed out to point and this'll be tight if he hits! That really would've been very tight
down the leg side and Bravo appeals once more
nice, loopy slower ball which he can't do anything with
goes for a swish but misses
turned to the on side
driven out to the off side and he finds mid-off. That's great placement
clatters it out to the off side
short, wide and cut to cover for a phat zero
full, straight and he digs it out
it's four! It's four whole runs off just the one delivery! Down onto the front foot he slaps it aerially over midwicket and that's four
fuller and he attempts the same shot but gets a bit of an inside, smudgy edge. Terrific throw from the deep though! That's outstanding fielding, but Collingwood's just home. He's so quick
outside off, he attempts a powerful shot but misses
slapped on the front foot out to cover
turned to short midwicket, in comes the throw but he's home. And the throw was too high
Prior lines up a muscular drive but can't quite time it. He shadows some strange-looking back-cuts and slogs after stealing a single
tries to smash it over midwicket but fails to connect properly
superb shot - cut backward of square out of the footholes
down the pitch and pulled over midwicket for four! Much more like it
what a catch! Collingwood pulls this over midwicket and Bravo, coming in a few steps, takes it low while diving slightly histrionically but spectacularly
plays and misses outside off
nice tickle off his pads
stroked along the ground through the covers
monstrous. Good stroke by Prior, lining up a slog over midwicket / wide long-on region for four
class. Inventive batting. A full toss which he paddled and scooped over short fine-leg. This is what is required

excellent, full ball which he tries to dig out but it clatters into his pads. Hang on - what's Broad up to here? He's almost level with Prior here! Bravo picks up and has all three stumps to aim at...but misses!
dug out to mid-on
slower ball outside off, Broad slaps it and is dropped by the diving short extra cover. Broad absolutely murdered that ball though
Broad smacks it to leg and they take a single. Prior would've been well gone had the throw hit
down leg, smacked to long-on
swung over midwicket
wide of the off stump, Prior tries to cut but can't manage it. Dar grins wryly as Prior intimates that it should've been a wide
steps to leg but can only crash a single to deep extra cover
smudged back to the bowler and Prior sets off...Bravo simply turns around, whips off the bails and watches Broad continue his way back to the pavilion
bosh! That's the ticket from Prior! Steps outside leg, opens up his stance and absolutely clobbers it over the top
full toss, cracked to mid-off
smudged through midwicket and Batty has two runs to his name. What a man

inn2.comm: outside off, Gayle has a sighter as he lets it go through...he won't do that very often
wide outside off, Gayle reaches for it without any footwork and doesn't make contact. Broad lucky that wasn't a wide
left alone again outside off
good line from Broad, on middle, Gayle defends back down the pitch
there's the first shot in anger, chopped away hard to backward point but it goes straight at Bopara
superb save from Bopara, Gayle flashes hard and makes good contact but Bopara gets across and saves the boundary
on off stump, turned out to square leg
clipped to square leg where Gareth Batty misfields by diving over the ball and giving away two. Simmons is away
big appeal from Anderson as Gayle is taken on the pad, he came down very late with the bat and barely played a shot but the ball pitched outside leg
opens the face outside off and guided away down to third man
well bowled, good line outside off and Simmons is beaten
nice shape from Anderson, full on off stump and shapes away a fraction as Simmons plays out to point
struck on the pad, appeal from Broad, but that pitched miles outside leg
on leg stump, during down to fine leg where Harmison is lurking
worked from middle and off into the leg side
another huge appeal from Broad, not a million miles away but heading down the leg side
this one's out! Broad gets an appeal answered as he strikes Gayle in front of off stump and the finger goes up. Nice shape back into the left hander and it looked fairly straight at first glance
starts with a positive drive straight to mid-off
too straight from Anderson and clipped away nicely to fine leg
good reply from the bowler, back outside off stump and Simmons plays forward into the off side
good line outside off, left alone through to Matt Prior
full outside off, leaves alone again
well bowled, Simmons is beaten this time as he tries to angle the ball down to third man
defended into the off side, good comeback after the early boundary in that over
on off stump, defended square on the off side
testing line, Sarwan steers this into the off side
touch shorter, Sarwan stands tall and punches back down the pitch where Broad gets a hand on it in his follow through
pushed out square on the off side
a little wider this time and left alone
good finish to a good over, on off stump and defended into the leg side
nearly dragged onto the stumps as he drives away from his body but the ball bounces safely away
on off stump, Simmons comes across his stumps and pushes up to mid on
onto the front foot, opens the face and defends to point
good bouncer from Anderson, over off stump and Simmons sways out of the line
nicely angled away down to third man
worked off middle stump with good timing, beats square leg and runs towards the boundary but Batty's dive prevents the four
defended straight down the pitch, the batsmen not getting much to attack so far
down the leg side, Broad's first wayward ball, and to add insult to injury Prior misses it so that's five to the total
slower ball full on off stump, driven hard but straight at short cover who has just been moved there
gets a bottom edge on this cut, Prior has no problem gathering this one
drifting towards leg stump, a strangled shout from Broad but nowhere near and there's two leg byes as fine leg runs around
better line, on off stump, Sarwan stands tall and defends
runs this away down to third man so he'll keep the strike
hint of movement into Sarwan, defended down to mid-on
driven sweetly up to mid-off...good time, just missing the placement
that's meat and drink to Sarwan, wide outside off and cut away through point for a welcome boundary
after the boundary takes the single as he angles to third man, good batting
well bowled, touch of extra bounce on off stump, but well played by Simmons as he takes one hand off the bat and opens the face
driven off the back foot into the covers where Ian Bell fields
outside edge but the slips have come out and it's too wide for Prior, races away down to third man and Simmons probably played it to be fair although not that fine
defended back to Broad in his follow through
plays this one wide of third man, Harmison gallops fine but can't stop them coming back for two
defended to backward point where Paul Collingwood is back on the field
stands tall and defends into the off side, not much else he can do with that tight line on off stump
plays away from his body, almost chops the ball into his stumps and then there's nearly a run out as well when Prior throws but Sarwan would have made it
good start, on off stump, worked out past midwicket
comes forward on off stump, pushed up to mid, 86mph from Harmison
big wide down the leg side, good stop from Prior at full stretch to his left
pushed into the off side
driven firmly up to mid-on, good areas from Harmison as the players would say
back of a length on off stump, defended into the off side
big appeal from Harmison, shapes back into Simmons who gets half a stride in and Aleem Dar says not out...might have been an inside edge, might have been outside the line
opens the face down to third man
good slower ball, draws Simmons forward and he defends to mid-off
full on off stump, pushed back to Broad in his follow through
excellent stuff from Broad, keeping the pressure on as Simmons defends back down the pitch
turned away off the stumps, a bit of a cutter from Broad, and it is worked down to fine leg
full on middle and off, worked out to midwicket
angled away into the off side but can't beat backward point
whipped away with a flourish but straight to the man at midwicket
he breaks the shackles with a powerful pull, goes up and over midwicket with off a ball that wasn't that short but he connected well
pushed out to backward point, that's the line and length for Harmison outside off
finds Collingwood hovering in that vital position at backward point again
comes down the pitch at Harmison, flicked off the hips down to Broad at fine leg who fumbles and means they complete a comfortable two
on leg stump, worked away through square and the man in the deep - Gareth Batty - can't prevent the second
leg stump again, wrong line from Anderson, and flicked away wide of mid-on for a boundary...some momentum building now for West Indies
wide outside of this time but Sarwan slaps it to cover and Anderson falls in a heap in his follow through...but he seems okay
ah, Sarwan's going now, just a hint of width and cracked away through the off side with power to beat the infield
driven sweetly off the back foot but picks out Shah at cover
turned out to midwicket but an expensive comeback over for Anderson
pulled around the corner
shorter delivery outside off which Sarwan tries to cut down to third man but misses. And so does Prior
pushed out to the off side
on middle stump, flicked to leg
good length outside off which is pushed out to the off side
pushed off the back foot
down the leg side
cut hard to point
good length, if a little too wide. It's pushed off the back foot
angled out to the off side
gives him width and it's very firmly smashed just short of Collingwood who, for once, misfields
climbs into another cut outside off
starts with one on middle stump which he wobbles off his pads
ooh, he plays and misses outside off. Nice, tight line from Mascarenhas and he tried to work it down to third man
another play-and-miss and Sarwan's furious at himself
worked to leg
again he turns it to leg and immediately sets off for a single - excellent pick-up and swivel and throw but he's safely home
pushed out to the off side
Batty starts with one on middle stump which is turned with a flick of the wrists
drives this out through cover
better and fuller length to which he punches back to the bowler
wristy and elegant flick to long-on
defended on the front foot
turned to leg
short of a length, punched to Batty at cover who prevents the single
angling into the right-hander who nudges to leg
played off the back foot to long-on
stroked to mid-off
Simmons comes forward, squeezing it out to point
flicked to leg
Simmons has gone for it and he's nailed it! What a blow. He came skipping down the pitch and lofted it over the top for a mighty six - great shot
holds this one back and he's nudging to leg
good length! That deceives Simmons a bit who crouches into a proddy defence on the back foot
down the pitch but Batty sends it flat and wide
punched back to Batty
flicked to midwicket
classic Sarwan shot. Wide enough to throw his hands at it, opening the face and just feathering it for four to third man
pushed out to mid-off but there's a complete mix-up in the middle! Bopara's thrown to the wicketkeeper's end - the wrong end! Good grief. That was poor
pushed out to the off side
mistimed this, attempting a big shot over midwicket but is too early on the shot
stroked to mid-off who is quite deep
plays and misses just outside the off stump
jumps into a punchy, back-foot stroke out to the off side
very straight, he stands tall while punching to leg
an effortless swish off his pads to a leg-side stray
pushed to Collingwood's right who fields well in his follow-through
cuts out to deep point
and it's blocked to end the over
fullish length punched back to the bowler
good line on middle and he again can't get it away
nice and full once more and he can't time this drive
don't bowl there! Gives him width and he fairly hammers it past point. So strong on the cut
pushed out to cover
angled to third man
pushes this out to the off side
nice line, defended on the back foot
too short but Simmons's pull finds deep midwicket
defended out to the off side
driven on the walk to long-off
crunched to short extra cover
too straight; nurdled through midwicket
pushed off his pads
angled down to third man
flicked to leg
good, straight ball which he can't get away
driven back to Mascarenhas
on the back foot, driving to long-on
excellent line spearing into the right hander who again just can't get it away
punched straight back to the bowler
lofting just short of long-on where Shah fields
pushed out to the off side
driven out to the off side
flicked just short of mid-on for West Indies' 100
short of a length, guided out to the off side
goes for a sweep and I think he's got a bottom edge on that, has he? Either way it beats Prior. Again
good, straight ball which Simmons again tries to sweep but misses
a stand-and-deliver slap out to the off side
tip-and-run shot to long-off
Collingwood spears this in on middle stump and it's comfortably fashioned through midwicket
flirted past the diving Strauss at short midwicket
drilled to mid-off
caressed to long-on
cheekily shovelled to the urgent reactions of short midwicket who, with urgent reactions, reacts urgently to shy at the stumps
cut out to deep extra cover
a good off-stump line is firmly defended
comes down the pitch and tries to whack him over cover but can't time it
short, wide and pushed out to the wide-brim-sun-hat-wearing Batty
a bouncer which Simmons tries to hook. Prior appeals but it's in vain
slapped to mid-off
driven to cover
gorgeous crunchy sound greets Sarwan's cut which brings up his fifty, and brings the crowd to their feet. What form this guy is in! Incredible stuff
swings this over midwicket and Broad's late to respond - has he seen it at all? He's into the sun here and despite a dive, he can't snaffle it
another crashing shot to leg - and again Broad's misfielded as he ran in and tried to pick it up one-handed. Very rare for him to make a mistake in the field
firmly driven back to Collingwood
nicely timed down the ground but Shah prevents four
driven inside out over cover and that's been a really useful over for West Indies. They do, however, need more of them
guided down to third man
comes right across outside off, ball takes the pad into the off side and there's a quick single as Sarwan responds
goes in the air over midwicket, more aggression now from both batsmen, but mid-on comes around and stops the boundary
slashed off the outside edge down to third man, slower ball from Harmison who hasn't bowled too badly so far
too wide, though, this time from Harmison and Simmons places it well through the off side with enough power to beat the deep cover
wild down the leg side, a good take from Prior prevents another boundary but Harmison now making my previous comment look a little silly
ends well, beaten outside off as he tries to dab down to third man

breakthrough! Sarwan falls, clipping a simple catch to midwicket where Andrew Strauss accepts it gleefully and that's a massive strike for England. The ball stopped a little from Collingwood and Sarwan turned it straight to the fielder
what a start, goes over the top of mid-on first ball and suddenly this ground is jumping. No looking, no playing himself in, he just launched this over the infield and away for four
more runs, down the leg side and it races away to the boundary...looks as though it has come off thigh pad or glove but it's given wides. England aren't best pleased about that
pushed down the ground to long off, suddenly the run-rate is rising
chipped out to midwicket
driven down the ground to long on
pushed in the air but very safely down the ground
round the wicket, driven into the covers
big appeal from Batty as Simmons sweeps, not the worst but he's a long way down
chopped down to short third man
swept hard out to deep square-leg
played into the off side
worked out through midwicket, Simmons wants two but they stay at a single
on off stump, turned to midwicket
flicked down to fine leg
too short from Mascarenhas, can't bowl there on this surface and that is pulled away by Simmons...is it six is it four? Looks like it just pitched inside but there's some confusion
goes for a sweep, taken on the pad
another sweep and misses, Prior whips off the bails
another wild swing, Simmons is starting to tick
tucked into the big gap at midwicket, a long single for Chanderpaul
tries to swing this over the leg side, taken on the pad but it's going well down leg
another appeal, this time he's struck on the pad outside off
that was always on the cards, Simmons had been swinging hard for a while and he picks out Anderson at deep midwicket who clings on...an important breakthrough
pushed into the off side, single down the ground
fairly loose drive to start with, thick inside edge through the leg side to open his account
play and miss outside off, no footwork and reaching away from his body
defended from off stump back to the bowler
flicked back down the pitch, England can build the pressure here
punched firmly down the pitch, Mascarenhas gets a hand on it and midwicket comes round to stop the single
well, that's one way to ease the pressure, an effortless free swing over mid-on and that finishes miles into the stands
solid defence to end the over
pushed back to the bowler
skips down the pitch and works out to deep square-leg
flatter on middle, worked out to midwicket
dragged down short, punched down to long on
worked down to long on, Pollard wanted the second but Shiv said no
flicked out to deep midwicket, keeps the strike
connects well with a pull but goes straight to deep square-leg
goes across his crease and tucks it between long long and deep square, an easy two and Chanderpaul decides that's enough
thick inside edge as he tries to drive, rolls into the off side
another inside edge into the pads and bobbles out to backward point
shovelled into the gap at midwicket, Harmison himself chases after it and slides to keep them to a single
well bowled, jagged back late at Pollard and it just bounces over the stumps
big turn there, ripping delivery outside off stump and Chanderpaul is beaten as he drives
angled into the off side gap
forced off the back foot, along the ground to midwicket
flicked through square leg this time and it's placed well enough to allow the batsmen back for a second
on off stump, Pollard defends coming forward
drifting onto leg stump, two more as he splits midwicket and square with just the right amount of power
round the wicket, driven in the air but short of cover...nearly a catch
worked along the ground down to one of the three deep fielders at long on
short and helped around the corner to short fine leg, was probably a run on there
short again and hammered square through the on side, Batty in the deep keeps them to a single
wide outside off and too wide
better line, in at the stumps, worked out to deep midwicket
what a strike, that goes into the middle section of the stand at long on again as Pollard shows his hitting power
poor, wide ball but a top shot - back-cutting for four. Brilliant
that is stunning! Absolutely brilliant from Chanderpaul. Down on one knee - almost both knees - he scooped underneath it and sent it sailing over fine leg for six. Special shot, that!
the crowd are alive now! Four more! An orthodox and powerfully struck four over extra cover. This is how you play a batting Powerplay!
shot! Four more to Chanderpaul, walking into another aerial extra-cover driven boundary
another! This is breathless cricket from Chanderpaul, standing tall and slapping it straight back past Harmison. My word - he absolutely drilled that
short, wide and Chanderpaul steps to leg and slaps it over extra cover for another four! That's how to play the Powerplay. Audacious, wonderful cricket
pulled to midwicket
on his legs and nudged through midwicket
short of a length, pulled around the corner to fine leg
got him this time! Chanderpaul went down on one knee and tried to flip him over midwicket but could only find a jubilant and lurking Strauss at square leg
outside off and he tries to cut, getting a bottom edge that falls short of Prior
stroked to cover where Anderson pulls off a fine stop
nicely cut - hang on. That's out! What a catch! Leant back and cut that quite powerfully but Bopara, at backward point, leaned forward and snaffled a very fine catch
back-cuts out to the off side
goes for a huge, crashing drive! He misses, but it was worth of an exclamation mark just to see how powerfully he hit the air. You could even hear the "whoosh"
a quick bouncer. Too good
a slow bouncer. Clever bowling, this. Paddled to the sprawling figure of Harmison
scuttles through low outside off
short and muscularly hook-pulled. It's gone for four. There's the power of the man. Think Flintoff. Mistimed shots scuttle over the line ...
stands tall and hammers this into the ground to mid-off
driven out past point, and Harmison has some yards to do from third man. A dive prevents four
good line, dropped out to the off side for a quick single
lines up a huge drive but can only manufacture a single to mid-on
nudged through midwicket and he steals the strike
pushed out to the off side
clunked to long-on
turned off his legs to short fine-leg, in comes the throw to Batty who makes a complete horlicks of it

lofts this over the top and this is straight through the hands of Steve Harmison who has dropped him! And it's gone for four! Brilliant stuff from big Steve there. Not only did he not catch it, but he let through four. Good grief
defended on the front foot
blocked
tries to work it to leg but it comes off the pads
nice touch, flicking it to leg
short of a length and whipped to long-on
down the leg side, but it's too full for Pollard to make anything of it. Flicked down to fine leg
chopped to point. No run
flicked to leg
short of a length and cut to point
patted to third man. Slower ball. More impressive thinking from Anderson
wide of the off stump, Pollard tries to drive but misses
shot! Oh that's a brilliant extra cover drive and seriously powerfully struck
top-edges this to Harmison at deep midwicket who steadies himself ... and takes a simple catch this time!
cut down to third man
slower ball wide of the off stump. Plays and misses
wide! What a waste
got him! Broad celebrates the wicket before the finger goes up - watch it, Stuart - and it scuttles through low on Ramdin who is late on it. That's plumb
